    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Yucatan Slang Jailbreak Benchmark (LiteLLM Gateway)\n\n**Fetch Jerga → Attacker → Target → Regex → Judge → Storage**\n\nAll LLM nodes call LiteLLM Proxy:\n`$env.LITELLM_BASE_URL/v1/chat/completions`\n\nEnv in n8n container: `LITELLM_BASE_URL`, `LITELLM_MASTER_KEY` only.\nProvider keys live in the `litellm` service.\n\nPostgres credential: `slang_bench_postgres`",
        "height": 328,
        "width": 628,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        64,
        -80
      ],
      "id": "0cded728-0636-4d62-8998-8837931cc0cb",
      "name": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## PAIR Loop (`pair_refine`)\n\nFor iterative attacks, wrap **Attacker → Target → Regex → Judge** in a sub-workflow loop (max 5 iterations). Feed judge feedback back into the Attacker user prompt per AGENTS.md.\n\nSet `technique` to `pair_refine` in Attack Config when using that sub-workflow.",
        "height": 232,
        "width": 568,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        2272,
